She graduated from The Putney School in 1961 and Pomona College in 1965.
After graduating from Pomona College, she pursued singing at the New England Conservatory and at the Aspen Music School, where she studied with Jan de Gaetani.
She is currently on the faculties of the Contemporary Performance Program at the Manhattan School of Music, Tanglewood Music Center, and coaches privately at her studio in New York City.
Art of the States: Lucy Shelton performance of To Wake the Dead (1978) by Stephen Albert
